DNS over HTTPS
Windows 10 & 11
Open the Settings app.
Go to Network & internet.
Click on Wi-Fi (or Ethernet).
Click on Hardware properties, or ignore this step if you clicked on Ethernet.
Click the Edit button next to DNS server assignment.
Select Manual.
Enable IPv4.
Enter 45.90.28.0 as Preferred DNS, then select On (manual template) and enter https://dns.nextdns.io/3aec68.
Enter 45.90.30.0 as Alternate DNS, then select On (manual template) and enter https://dns.nextdns.io/3aec68.
Click Save.
